An airport is a place where airplanes usually operate. Many sovereign countries have more than one major airport. This is due to the fact that many people usually travel by air. However, it is important for us to note the fact that there are some European countries that do not have any airport. Let us carefully identify some of these countries.
1. Monaco
This country is located in the western region of Europe. The official name of this country is the Principality of Monaco. The Principality of Monaco is one of the major countries that do not have any airport. Many people in Monaco use the Nice Cote dâ€™Azur Airport in order to travel by air. However, it should be said that this airport is located in France.
2. Liechtenstein
This is the second European country on this list. The official name of this country is the Principality of Liechtenstein. There is no airport in Liechtenstein. Some people in Liechtenstein usually move to Germany in order to travel by air.
3. Andorra
It is important to point out that this is the third sovereign country on this list. The official name of this nation is the Principality of Andorra. There is no airport in Andorra.


